C002771 / The Hague

Skills, knowledge, experience required:

Higher vocational training in a relevant discipline (Telecommunications and Digital Communications or Electronic or Electrical Engineering) with 3 years of post-related experience;
OR a secondary educational qualification with 5 years of post-related experience;
At least three years of experience on SHF and UHF Satellite Communication (SATCOM) Systems;
Extensive experience with:
RF Systems and active and passive components including antennas, low noise and power amplifiers, up and down converters, combiners and splitters, circulators, directional couplers, switches;
Antenna tracking systems, SATCOM modems including Spread Spectrum Modems (SSMA, CDMA, EPM), smart Multiplexers, UPS, Diesel generators, Heating Ventilation and Air Conditioning (HVAC) and measurement equipment (spectrum analysers);
Network analyzers, oscilloscopes, power meters, digicom analysers, multimeters, sweeping RF generators, DVM and Multimeters, Digital and analog recorders interfaced with PC for data acquisition and post elaboration, logic state analyzers, datacom analyzers), test loop translators, EPROM programmers;
Modern analogue and digital transmission techniques;
HW and SW use and management of Personal Computers and Work Stations (e.g. capability to assemble a system, install Operating Systems and software);
Extensive experience in:
Soldering tools for discrete components and SMD;
Switching systems their application, operation and maintenance;
Experience with:
HF, UHF and DLOS communication systems;
Mathematical tools (e.g. MATLAB, Scilab or GNU Octave);
Laboratory, simulation and automated test & measurement systems software and hardware (e.g. Simulink, BenchVue, LabView, LabWindows, and C for Virtual Instruments (CVI));
Experience in:
Working in a demanding technical and scientific environment;
Technical supervisory;
Communication IP networks technology;
Installation and setup of communication equipment including IP routers and switches;
Methodologies, tools and products for laboratory and field testing of communications systems, networks and equipment;
Preparing training and delivering training;
Hands-on experience in configuration, operation, management and trouble-shooting of local and wide area networks, including routing, naming and addressing;
Advanced and working knowledge of:
Standard Automatic Data Processing;
Word Processing;
Spreadsheet;
Graphics Presentation;
Database;
E-mail Clients/Web Browsers;
Web Content Management;
A very good understanding of telecommunications / network / information technology solutions & products including management and installations;
Ability to:
Write code (e.g. in C, Basic or other programming languages) to drive test equipment, manage databases, webpages, workflows and documents production allowing as well interaction amongst different programs (e.g. amongst Adobe and/or MS Outlook and/or MS Excel and/or MS Access, even simultaneously amongst all the listed products);
Communicate effectively orally and in writing with good briefing skills;
Familiarity with accounting and control procedures for classified equipment.

Desirable:

A University degree in a communications related scientific or engineering discipline;
A Bachelor degree (or vocational training) at a nationally recognised/certified University in Telecommunications Engineering and Digital Communications or related subject (e.g. Electronic or Electrical Engineering) with at least 8 years of post-related experience;
OR the lack of a degree may be compensated by a lower academic qualification combined with at least eleven 11 years of experience and the demonstration of particular abilities or experience of relevance to this post, or with a related subject;
Three years practical experience with:
NATO SATCOM systems;
NCISS / NC.

Duties/role:

Assisting in:
Experimental investigations including preparation for experiments, the collection of scientific data and supporting information during experiments, and in the processing and analysing experimental data;
Fielding of prototype systems for operational evaluation;
System analysis studies;
Preparation of scientific reports;
Preparing and conducting laboratory measurements and field trials, and analysing and documenting the results;
Being responsible for the operation, maintenance, upgrading and documentation (including preparation of specifications and initiation of purchase) of scientific laboratories and testbeds;
Designing, developing, documenting and constructing experimental or prototype experimental SATCOM equipment (e.g. Software Defined Radio, digital network, SATCOM equipment and systems, Digital Line Of Sight);
Liaising on SATCOM related matters with internal NCIA stakeholders and external NATO bodies, Nations, and Industry;
Deputizing for higher grade staff, if required;
Performing:
Ad hoc tasks related to the Branch responsibilities;
Any other duties as may be required by direct Management;
Other duties as may be required.

